-- OTP Bank Gains First Day in Three After German Confidence Rises
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-23T09:36:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-23/otp-bank-gains-first-day-in-three-after-german-confidence-rises.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  advanced for the
first time in three days after business confidence in  Germany ,
 Hungary ’s biggest trading partner, climbed more than economists
forecast to the highest in seven months.  The shares of Hungary’s largest lender increased as much as
0.8 and traded 0.4 percent higher at 3,942 forint by 10:18 a.m.
in Budapest. The stock fell 1.7 percent earlier today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
